\section*{\emph{Recommendation}}

The problem Cory identified appears to exist in high-rate files from
many projects. See, for example, CSETrf06hrt.nc, 19:33:00\textendash 19:53:00.
Although it is often masked by dominating relative-wind fluctuations,
it seems worth eliminating. The proposed variable uses a complementary-filter
approach similar to that used for the horizontal wind and would seem
to be a useful change to standard processing. It will be particularly
useful when processing at high rate.

